The paper focuses on the task of routing newly posted questions to potential answerers in Community Question Answering sites (CQAs), which involves leveraging both graph structural information and textual information from question tags. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR) which deals with search and recommendation tasks, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) which deals with graph-based analysis of social networks, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) which deals with natural language processing, Statistical Learning (cs.LG) which deals with machine learning methods, and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) which deals with audio and text processing.
